Commentary Text: Nortje to W Saha, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! He's mishit this, mid-off in business and Iyer takes it. Length delivery, seemed to have stopped on Saha, who went through the lofted drive a touch early and skied this, a sitter for Iyer's standards even though it had a lot of hang time. Wherever you are, a standing ovation for Saha please. To replace a star striker like Bairstow after a gut-wrenching loss to KXIP and to come out and take on the likes of Nortje and Rabada in the powerplay is no easy thing. Indian fans will also be keen on those stretches Saha was doing with the Australian tour in mind, Hope it's nothing to worry! W Saha c Shreyas Iyer b Nortje 87(45) [4s-12 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Pant, out Caught by (sub)Goswami! That's a full and wide one outside off-stump, too far outside the tramline, big appeal as Pant has a swipe at that, but that's been called a wide. Warner has gone up to the third umpire, using up a review either for the dismissal or the wide. Definitely looked like there was bat in real-time. Correction - sounded like bat. I see a spike as soon as he reaches the bat - so it does look like it's out. Might be the best review of all time! Awaiting the official decision. It's been reversed! It's out! The umpire can't believe it, and eventually, disbelievingly crosses his arms and raises the finger. Pant c (sub)Goswami b Sandeep Sharma 36(35) [4s-3 6s-1]
